Description: Papyrus (two large and three very small fragments). Recto: ends of five lines of a demotic document of sale of a cow (more or less direct continuation of 10846/1) ; first five lines of a demotic document of lease. Verso: first four names and traces of a fifth of the witnesses of the second text. Second text is dated to year 3 of Hakoris (391/0 BC).
